<div class="blog-faq">
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>How long does it take to see final results after plastic surgery?</h3>
<p>Most patients see significant improvement within 1 to 3 months after surgery, but final results are typically apparent at 6 to 12 months. Healing is a gradual process, and tissues continue to settle and refine over time. Patience during the recovery period is essential for appreciating the full benefits of your procedure.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Can I see before and after photos during my consultation?</h3>
<p>Yes, Dr. Johar's clinic provides access to an extensive gallery of before and after photos during your consultation. You can also view photos online at the <a href="https://www.theaesthetic.in/gallery-plastic-reconstructive-surgeon-noida-up/">gallery page</a>. Reviewing photos of patients with similar concerns to yours helps you set realistic expectations.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>What if I am not happy with my results?</h3>
<p>While complications and dissatisfaction are uncommon with experienced surgeons, they can occur. If you have concerns about your results, contact your surgeon promptly. Most issues can be addressed through minor revisions or non-surgical treatments. Open communication with your surgeon ensures that any concerns are addressed promptly and effectively.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Will my plastic surgery results look natural?</h3>
<p>When performed by a skilled surgeon, plastic surgery results should look natural and complement your overall appearance. Dr. Manoj K Johar specializes in achieving subtle, natural-looking outcomes that enhance your features without appearing artificial. During your consultation, discuss your desire for natural results so your surgeon can plan accordingly.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>How do swelling and bruising affect my results?</h3>
<p>Swelling and bruising are normal parts of the healing process and can temporarily obscure your results. Swelling typically subsides significantly within the first 2 to 4 weeks, though residual swelling may persist for several months depending on the procedure. Bruising usually resolves within 1 to 2 weeks. Your surgeon will guide you on what to expect during each phase of recovery.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Can I see different angles in before and after photos?</h3>
<p>A comprehensive gallery should include photos from multiple angles to give you a complete view of the results. At Dr. Johar's clinic, the <a href="https://www.theaesthetic.in/gallery-plastic-reconstructive-surgeon-noida-up/">before and after gallery</a> includes frontal, side, and oblique views for most procedures, allowing you to evaluate results from every perspective.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>How can I maintain my plastic surgery results long-term?</h3>
<p>Maintaining a stable weight, protecting your skin from sun damage, following a healthy lifestyle, and considering maintenance treatments like Botox or fillers can help preserve your results. Regular follow-up appointments with Dr. Johar allow for ongoing monitoring and personalized recommendations for long-term maintenance.</p>
</div>
</div>

